Sentencas: Gold is generally considered to be inert for electrochemical reactions in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Gold particle effect on high temperature oxygen reduction reaction via lanthanum strontium cobaltite ferrite electrocatalyst

Sentencas: It is thus used as the standard current collector to characterize the catalytic activity of various cathode materials including the state-of-the-art lanthanum strontium cobalt iron oxide (LSCF).
Titulo: Gold particle effect on high temperature oxygen reduction reaction via lanthanum strontium cobaltite ferrite electrocatalyst

Sentencas: This work shows that gold is not inert but active for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) via LSCF.
Titulo: Gold particle effect on high temperature oxygen reduction reaction via lanthanum strontium cobaltite ferrite electrocatalyst

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity relaxation measurement shows that scattered gold particles on LSCF surface can greatly increase the ORR rate.
Titulo: Gold particle effect on high temperature oxygen reduction reaction via lanthanum strontium cobaltite ferrite electrocatalyst

Sentencas: Gold improves the chemical oxygen surface exchange coefficient by a factor up to 27.5.
Titulo: Gold particle effect on high temperature oxygen reduction reaction via lanthanum strontium cobaltite ferrite electrocatalyst

Sentencas: The improvement is much high at reduced temperature from 800 to 650 ?C.
Titulo: Gold particle effect on high temperature oxygen reduction reaction via lanthanum strontium cobaltite ferrite electrocatalyst

Sentencas: In addition, gold particles with smaller size show better performance in enhancing the ORR activity.
